<item>
            <title>[SPR-2650] Spring 2.0 RC4 JMS logging issue/request for class SingleConnectionFactory</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2650</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know this may seem trivial, but going from RC3 to RC4, there has been a change in log messages being printed out. Specifically org.springframework.jms.connection.SingleConnectio nFactory.createConnection() has the following code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public Connection createConnection() throws JMSException {&lt;br/&gt;
synchronized (this.connectionMonitor) {&lt;br/&gt;
if (this.connection == null) {&lt;br/&gt;
initConnection();&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
if (logger.isInfoEnabled()) {&lt;br/&gt;
logger.info(&quot;Established shared JMS Connection: &quot; + this.target);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
return this.connection;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This logger.info() statement is being printed out to the logfiles less than once a second. Can this log statement be changed to a DEBUG level instead of an INFO level? Having a log message print out at this kind of frequency renders the log file as useless. I think DEBUG would be more appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I checked in RC3 and the debug statement in the same createConnection() method was at DEBUG level.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Jim&lt;/p&gt;</description>
